      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section id="StartUpCheckOnOneUnit-20D8C3C2"
                  platform="WxW"
                  class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Start Up Check</title>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note "> The DC capacitors needs
to be charged before the inverter input switch is closed.</note>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the external source of the DC input power is available.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
                  <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
                  <note conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/autostart_start-up"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all LEDâ€™s
on the front panel illuminates. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second, if the unit did
not start from the autostart. After a few seconds or if any key is
pressed the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power
...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 8 key</b> to check the DC voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 5 key</b> to check the DC current.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number 9 key</b> to check that the inverter output
voltage is within tolerance. Check that the green inverter LED on
the mimic diagram is illuminated.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm the alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section: <xref href="#./BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <section id="BypassOperationCheckOnOneUnit-AA6BEEEC"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Bypass Operation Check</title>
         <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/output_energized"
                          class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note class="- topic/note ">Check that the position of the external manual
bypass switch is <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</note>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the external bypass input switch. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the EN (BYP SSW) input switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the yellow inverter LED on the mimic diagram is
illuminated, indicating that the inverter is synchronized with the
bypass mains.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the green LED before the static switch EN (upstream)
on the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the bypass mains
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:<ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_DD00545782.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-5AF57FF1/Switch-to-bypass_1220236"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch back to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_DD00545781.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-5AF6A01C/Switch-to-normal_1220236"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section: <xref href="#./SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
                        scope="local"
                        type="section"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
      <section id="SetManualBypassSwitchesToAuto-AA6C103D"
               platform="PxW WxW"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Set Manual Bypass Switch to UPS</title>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to bypass operation:</p>
               <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_DD00545782.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-5AF57FF1/Switch-to-bypass_1220236"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the green LED after the inverter (downstream) on
the mimic diagram is illuminated, indicating that the inverter output
is available and within tolerance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">If the inverter output is available and within tolerance, switch
the external manual bypass switch to the position <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">UPS</b>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch the unit to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_DD00545781.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-5AF6A01C/Switch-to-normal_1220236"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p "> Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Continue with the section:<xref href="1220236_Connecting_the_Output_Distribution_CPT_DD00561512.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="concept"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
